ownedRule.name: array type needs a non-array type

ownedComment.body: Each array type in your model requires a corresponding non-array type to be defined.

specification.body: context WSDLType inv: array->notEmpty() implies nonArray->notEmpty()

ownedRule.name: a web service parameter can not be of type collection

ownedComment.body: A web service parameter can NOT be a collection type You'll need to model an array instead.

specification.body: context WebServiceParameter inv : return = false implies type.collectionType = false

ownedRule.name: a web service operation return type can not be a collection type

ownedComment.body: A web service operation's return type can NOT be a collection type, you'll need to model an array instead.

specification.body: context WebServiceOperation inv: exposed implies returnType.collectionType = false

ownedComment.body: A web service can not have more than one operation with the same name, please check the names of your web service operations.

ownedRule.name: wsdl types cannot have private attributes

ownedComment.body: All attributes must have a public visibility.

specification.body: context WSDLType inv : attributes -> forAll(visibility = 'public' or visibility='protected')

ownedRule.name: wsdl types cannot have private navigable association ends.

ownedComment.body: All navigable association ends must have a public visibility.

specification.body: context WSDLType inv : associationEnds -> forAll(otherEnd.navigable implies otherEnd.visibility = 'public' or otherEnd.visibility = 'protected')

ownedRule.name: webservice operation names must be unique

ownedComment.body: Webservice operation names must be unique within each package/namespace.

ownedRule.name: a web service operation exception must be a web fault

ownedComment.body: Each web service operation exception must have the web fault stereotype.

specification.body: context WebServiceOperation inv: exposed implies webFaultOnAllExceptions = true

ownedRule.name: wsdl fault types must be an exception

ownedComment.body: Each WSDLType which is a WebFault must also be an Exception.

ownedRule.name: wsdl fault types must be thrown from a webservice operation

ownedComment.body: Each WSDLType which is a WebFault must be thrown by a webservice operation.
